Arele and some

00:07:35.260 --> 00:07:38.330
of her poems are dedicated
her brother Arele.

00:07:38.330 --> 00:07:42.820
But he was torn out of her hands
and she never saw him again.

00:07:42.820 --> 00:07:46.390
Rivka spent two years
in the Vilna ghetto

00:07:46.390 --> 00:07:50.840
where she met the great
Yiddish poet Abraham Sutzkever.

00:07:50.840 --> 00:07:56.340
Ten years older than Rivka
Sutzkever was already a recognized

00:07:56.340 --> 00:07:58.190
Yiddish poet.

00:07:58.190 --> 00:08:03.150
When Rivka told Sutzkever that she
herself composed poems Sutzkever

00:08:03.150 --> 00:08:09.210
said, keep it up that's what
will keep you alive and it did.

00:08:09.210 --> 00:08:10.510
When Rivka was sent

00:08:10.510 --> 00:08:13.640
to the Kaiserwald Concentration
Camps she continued

00:08:13.640 --> 00:08:15.350
to compose poems.

00:08:15.350 --> 00:08:21.640
It's been said that at the
Warsaw uprising the cry went

00:08:21.640 --> 00:08:25.450
out [foreign language],
Jews don't be despaired.

00:08:25.450 --> 00:08:31.150
And in that same spirit of the
Nazis can control our bodies,

00:08:31.150 --> 00:08:34.300
but they can't control
our spirit the women

00:08:34.300 --> 00:08:40.530
of this concentration camp decided
to entertain the inmates every day.

00:08:40.530 --> 00:08:45.300
So at the end of every grueling
workday there were three women

00:08:45.300 --> 00:08:50.480
who entertained the
inmates, one sang, one danced

00:08:50.480 --> 00:08:54.200
and one composed a poem
and recited it that day.

00:08:54.200 --> 00:09:00.040
It was Rivka who composed a
poem and recited it every day.

00:09:00.040 --> 00:09:03.250
This is Rivka's description
of that experience.

00:09:03.250 --> 00:09:05.550
It's called the Dermonung.

00:09:08.040 --> 00:09:09.840
Remembrance first in Yiddish.

00:09:09.840 --> 00:09:41.040
[ Speaking Foreign Language ]

00:09:41.040 --> 00:09:43.830
